headline: Boeing (BA) Valuation Check as Weak Sales, Cash Burn and Dilution Fears Pressure Investor Sentiment
summary: Boeing (BA) is back in focus as fresh reports underline two years of weak unit sales, ongoing cash burn and negative operating cash flow, all of which are sharpening investor worries about future dilution. See our latest analysis for Boeing. The latest concerns are landing just as Boeing’s 1 month share price return of 5.64% has given way to a weaker 3 year total shareholder return of 10.67%.
